  "firstAcquaintance": "Despite being a half-breed, her outstanding strength made her the chieftain of the Bloodcow tribe. She frequently leads her tribe in territorial disputes against the boar-kin.",
  "personality": "Rough and hot-tempered with a stubborn streak. She often refuses to listen to reason. But if you manage her moods right, she is really just a simple-minded hothead at heart.",
  "like": "The Minotaur King, fresh fruit",
  "familiarData": "The child of the former Bloodcow tribe chieftain, born from forcing a male slave. Although her appearance leans more toward a human form, the Bloodcow tribe values strength above all, and she still bears some minotaur features, so she was not driven out of the tribe.\nAfter the chieftain died, she defeated all her siblings to become the new chieftain, inheriting her predecessor's legacy by occupying the Dragonbone Gorge, which brought her into conflict with the boar-kin.\nShe participated in a coup within the boar-kin kingdom, but because her actions diverged from the Minotaur King's wishes, she was expelled from minotaur territory. She and some of the Bloodcow tribe members became wanderers. However, she deeply respects the Minotaur King and hopes for the minotaur race to reclaim the glory of the second-generation Demon Lord era. What she does not know is that the Minotaur King has no desire to challenge the third-generation Demon Lord.\nShe has a bull-headed temperament, stubbornly persisting in everything she does and refusing to listen to others. But if you distract her and give her a scare, she will calm down and actually listen to what people have to say.",
  "familiarUnlockLevel": 5,
